messages.user_message: What is the appropriate printing speed for 3D printing using fused deposition modeling with polylactic acid (PLA) mixed with Akermanite?
messages.assistant_response: The appropriate printing speed for 3D printing using fused deposition modeling (FDM) with polylactic acid (PLA) mixed with Akermanite is 10 mm/s. This parameter was used for printing composite scaffolds with 70% porosity, using a nozzle diameter of 400 μm and a layer thickness of 400 μm at a printing temperature of 210 °C [source: reference_117.pdf, page 2].

messages.user_message: What is the appropriate layer height for 3D printing using fused deposition modeling with polylactic acid (PLA) mixed with Akermanite?
messages.assistant_response: The appropriate layer height for 3D printing using fused deposition modeling (FDM) with polylactic acid (PLA) mixed with Akermanite is 400 μm (0.4 mm) [source: reference_117.pdf, page 2].

messages.user_message: What is the appropriate nozzle diameter for 3D printing using fused deposition modeling with polylactic acid (PLA) mixed with Akermanite?
messages.assistant_response: The appropriate nozzle diameter for 3D printing using fused deposition modeling (FDM) with polylactic acid (PLA) mixed with Akermanite is 400 μm (0.4 mm) [reference_117.pdf, page 2].

messages.user_message: What is the appropriate nozzle temperature for 3D printing using fused deposition modeling with polylactic acid (PLA) mixed with carbon fibre (CF)?
messages.assistant_response: The appropriate nozzle temperature for 3D printing using fused deposition modeling (FDM) with polylactic acid (PLA) mixed with carbon fibre (CF) is 230 °C. This temperature yields the highest tensile properties for both PLA and PLA-CF composites [reference_181.pdf, page 1].
